07/10/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Two multinational NATO military exercises began in Albania on Friday (October 5th) and will continue until October 30th.
Seven NATO members are participating, as well as 12 partner countries, including Albania and Macedonia.
In other news Friday, NATO Military Committee Chairman General Ray Henault said that Albania.
Croatia and Macedonia are making significant progress in reforming their armies.
However, he added, the Alliance must also consider achievements in the economic and political spheres as it decides on their bids for membership.
Henault is visiting Romania to discuss issues related to international co-operation and security, including Romania's participation in NATO missions.
(Makfax - 06/10/07;
MIA - 05/10/07)
